{
  "texts": [
    "• The coefficients of the secret polynomial s are chosen uniformly at random from {0, 1}: this is known as uniform binary secret.",
    "• The coefficients of the secret polynomial s are chosen in {-1, 0, 1} with a restriction that exactly h of them are 1 or -1, and the rest are all zeros: this is known as fixed Hamming weight secret.",
    "The exact method for sampling the nonzero entries may vary depending on the implementation.",
    "• For a fixed Hamming weight secret such that the Hamming weight is small (e.g., h < 0.25 • n), keys chosen from this distribution are called sparse secret keys.",
    "We discuss sparse secrets in the following subsection."
  ]
}